    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make Government Funds Available for Victims & Families of Terrorist Attacks",
        "additional_details": "Financial Funds need to be made available for victims and their families , and those who have been affected by incidents of terrorism in the United Kingdom. There needs to be a special fund set up to help these people, and their families who need to take time off work, to look after family members, general living expenses, and specialist care.\r\nThis is the least we can do as a nation, to help people who need it the most. After experiencing such life affecting atrocities!",
        "background": "I was shocked to recently learn that there is \u2018No\u2019 financial funding help for victims or their families of terrorist attacks in the U.K. \r\nIn light of the Manchester Arena bombing, and the 22 victims, London Bridge Attack, Westminster Attack, Finsbury Park Attack in 2017 we should be helping.",
